      "correctIndex": 1,
      "misconceptionFeedback": "⚠️ Common misconception! Because velocity is squared in Ek = ½mv², doubling the speed means the kinetic energy is multiplied by 2² = 4. Speed has a much bigger effect on KE than mass does.",
